name: Ms. Vidya Rao Karane
degree_type: Dr Vidya is working at Dr L H Hiranandani hospital as a consultant Physiotherapist since July 2010.Prior to this she has extended her services to Breach Candy Hospital. She has been a physiotherapist for sports of swimming in Common Wealth Youth Games (CYG), 2009. She has also worked for camps organized by Multiple Sclerosis Society and has worked as a physiotherapist for an orthopedic camp held at Madhya Pradesh.She has the expertise of handling patients with Neurological disorders (Any disorder of brain and spinal cord injury). She has been specially trained for handling patients with Stroke, Spinal Cord Injuries, Parkinson’s disease and Multiple Sclerosis. Her other field of interest includes Pain management, Cardio respiratory physiotherapy, Women’s health, Geriatric health and balance training for elderlyShe has also received training through various workshops and conferences like Motor Control Theory, Neurodevelopmental Therapy, the bobath and the brunnstrom approach for treating hemiplegic patients. She attended the training session for Sensory Integration, also cervical spine manipulation training.Her field of research is Stroke, Low back pain due to lumbar spondylosis and Osteoporosis.
